title: Dish says SpaceX’s Starlink 5G interference study is flawed
summary: Dish Network and others pushing for permission to use 12 GHz spectrum for 5G said July 7 that SpaceX’s study on how it would severely disrupt its broadband customers is “scientifically and logically flawed.”

title: Space Force effort to open doors to private sector is a slow go
summary: Companies seeking help through the Space Systems Command 'Front Door' initiative can expect to wait several days for a response

title: NASA Updates Coverage for Webb Telescope’s First Images Reveal
summary: NASA, in partnership with ESA (European Space Agency) and CSA (Canadian Space Agency), will release the James Webb Space Telescope’s first full-color images and spectroscopic data during a live broadcast beginning at 10:30 a.m. EDT Tuesday, July 12, from NASA’s Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Maryland.

title: Stellar Ventures unveils $23 million early-stage fund
summary: Stellar Ventures unveiled a fund July 7 with $23 million to invest in early-stage space-related startups.

title: Defense Innovation Unit selects contractors to build hybrid space network
summary: Anduril, Aalyria, Atlas Space and Enveil won contracts for the Defense Innovation Unit's hybrid space architecture program
